    <text>
        <body>
            
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="cww.01080.001.jpg"/>
            
            <div1 type="petition" subtype="handwritten" corresp="#rg21">

                <div2 type="document" subtype="handwritten">
                    <opener>
                        <salute>To <persName>John A Smith</persName> <choice><abbr>Esq</abbr><expan>Esquire</expan></choice> Clerk of the Circuit Court of the <placeName>District of Columbia</placeName></salute>
                        <salute>Sir</salute>
                    </opener>
                    <p><persName>Thomas Green</persName> of <placeName>Washington</placeName> having claim to the service of <persName><choice><orig>Oranange</orig><reg>Orange</reg></choice> Barber</persName> &#38; <persName>Helen Barber</persName> &#38; having failed to file his schedule or Petition in accordance with the provisions of the Act of Congress concerning Emancipation approved <date when="1862-04-16">April 16, 1862</date>. The said <persName>Orange Barber</persName> filed this his Petition for himself &#38; his wife <persName>Helen</persName> in pursuance of the act of amendatory to said act approved <date when="1862-07-12">July 12, 1862</date> in lieu of said Petition of said <persName>Thomas Green</persName></p>
                    <p>Petitioner says that he &#38; his said wife have resided within the <placeName>District of Columbia</placeName> since before the <date when="1862-04-16">16th of April 1862</date> &#38; still reside therein by the consent of said <persName>Thomas Green</persName></p>
                    <ab>Schedule Age of <persName>Orange Barber</persName> 55 about 5 1/2 ft Copper Color. <persName>Helen Barber</persName> about 65 years 5 ft high Copper Color</ab>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>his X mark <persName>Orange Barber</persName></signed><lb/>
                        <signed>her X mark <persName>Helen Barber</persName></signed><lb/>
                        In presence of<lb/>
                        <signed><persName>Geo E. H. Day</persName></signed>
                    </closer>
                </div2>                        
                                        
                <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="cww.01080.002.jpg"/>
                
                <div2 type="cover" subtype="handwritten">
                    <div3 type="section">
                        <ab><choice><abbr>pd</abbr><expan>paid</expan></choice></ab>
                    </div3>
                    <div3 type="section">
                        <ab><persName>Orange Barber</persName></ab>
                        <ab><persName>Helen Barber</persName> Petition</ab>
                    </div3>
                    <div3 type="section">
                        <ab>Certificate issued <date when="1862-07-26">26 July 1862</date></ab>
                    </div3>
                    <div3 type="section">
                        <ab>Filed <date when="1862-07-25">25 July 1862</date></ab>
                    </div3>
                    
                   <div3 type="section">
                        <p>The Commissioners satisfied on the testimony of <persName>John Feuses</persName> of the truth of the matters herein stated order that the same be so certified to the Clerk of the Circuit Court of the <placeName>District of Columbia</placeName></p>
                        <closer>
                                <signed><persName>Wm. R. Woodward</persName> clerk</signed>
                            <dateline><date when="1862-07-25">July 25, 1862</date></dateline>
                            </closer>
                        </div3>
                    
                    <div3 type="section">
                        <ab>Recorded in Manumission Record No. 2 folio 69</ab>
                    </div3>
                    </div2>
            </div1>
           
            <!-- Evidence pertaining to the case begins here. -->
            
            <pb xml:id="leaf002r" facs="cww.01080.003.jpg"/>
            <div1 type="evidence" corresp="#rg217" subtype="handwritten">
                <dateline><date when="1862-07-25">July 25</date>.</dateline>
                
                <div2 type="procedural">
                    <ab><persName>Orange Barber</persName></ab>
                    <ab><persName>Helen Barber</persName></ab>
                    <ab>servants of<persName>Thomas Green</persName></ab>
                </div2>
                
                <div2 type="testimony">
                    <p><persName>John <unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#jc">Feues</unclear></persName> know these servants as Mr <persName>Thomas Greens</persName>. there the last 12 years. no doubt of it.</p>
                </div2>
                
                <div2 type="procedural">
                    <ab>Certificate ordered</ab>
                </div2>
                                                
                <pb xml:id="leaf002v" facs="cww.01080.004.jpg"/>
                
                <div2 type="cover">
                    <ab><persName>Orange Barber</persName></ab>
                    <ab><persName>Helen Barber</persName></ab>
                    <ab><date when="1862-07-25">July 25</date></ab>
                </div2>
            </div1>            
